The article discusses a series of attacks carried out by militia groups affiliated with Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) against US personnel and facilities in Iraq and Syria. These attacks involved the use of unmanned aerial systems and indirect fire, resulting in injuries to US service members and the death of a contractor. In response, the US conducted targeted strikes on facilities in eastern Syria used by the IRGC and affiliated groups. The strikes were aimed at establishing deterrence, protecting US personnel, degrading ongoing attacks, and deterring further Iranian-backed attacks. The military action was carried out in accordance with the President's constitutional authority and international law. The President provides this report to Congress to fulfill the requirements of the War Powers Resolution.